{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016WLVJL1Yd7yfuRvNT1QTBH","type":"tool_result","content":"bb61e6e wiki: group: frontmatter sections the generated index.md (SLICE-0073)\n1f72d48 wiki: generate per-project index.md at wiki sync (SLICE-0072)\ne7d8018 wiki: required summary field on all 5 template schemas (SLICE-0071)\n16ee54a ralph: audit-fix loop bundle (8 plans) + loop state\nf78cf7b wiki: scope test script to tests/ so bun run test skips bundled qmd/ (item 8)\n---\n{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0071: required summary field on all 5 template schemas, rendered atop the body, exposed as the --summary create flag\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Add `summary: { type: string, required: true, min: 10, max: 200 }` to the schema block of all five templates/*.md (prd, slice, decision, doc, handoff)\",\n        \"Render a summary line at the top of each template body (under the id/title line)\",\n        \"Confirm createGeneric auto-derives the --summary flag and validation enforces min/max; omitting --summary fails with a missing-required-field error\",\n        \"Update existing test fixtures / create calls that now miss the required summary so the suite stays green\",\n        \"Add a test: create with --summary succeeds and renders the line; create without --summary fails; an existing artifact lacking summary still validates on read (grandfathered)\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0072: generate a static per-project index.md at wiki sync (id, title, summary, status from frontmatter)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"In src/cli/verbs/sync.ts, after the qmd embed loop, scan every artifact under projects/<project>/, read frontmatter (id, title, summary, status, group)\",\n        \"Write projects/<project>/index.md as plain markdown (table or list), sorted by kind then id, linked ids, no prose duplication, NO Dataview/Bases\",\n        \"Idempotent overwrite each sync; create must never write index.md\",\n        \"Add a test against a TEMP vault fixture (follow existing tests/ patterns): sync writes index.md listing the artifacts; re-running yields identical bytes\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0073: group: frontmatter sections the generated index.md (no folders)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Add optional `group: { type: string }` to the kind schemas\",\n        \"In the index.md generator, section artifacts under ## <group> headings; ungrouped fall under ## General\",\n        \"No physical folder nesting; path-containment guard unchanged\",\n        \"Add a test (temp vault): grouped artifacts appear under their group heading, ungrouped under General\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"chore\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0074: strip template-bleed from all 5 templates (source fix only)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Read SLICE-0058 first to avoid duplicating the renderer work it already did on existing files\",\n        \"Edit all five templates/*.md: remove the Templater <%* ... %> comment block, the INPUT[select(...)] status widget, and the instructional > blockquotes under each section\",\n        \"Keep clean fixed section headings the author fills, and the summary line added in item 1\",\n---TEMPLATES---\ndecision.md  2.2K\ndoc.md  1.6K\nhandoff.md  1.8K\nprd.md  3.3K\nslice.md  3.6K","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a24f960-2834-4b0d-82fe-20b82465aea9","uuid":"b896ff5d-d68e-429c-9a8e-59011ed0ac9c","timestamp":"2026-06-23T16:46:53.077Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"bb61e6e wiki: group: frontmatter sections the generated index.md (SLICE-0073)\n1f72d48 wiki: generate per-project index.md at wiki sync (SLICE-0072)\ne7d8018 wiki: required summary field on all 5 template schemas (SLICE-0071)\n16ee54a ralph: audit-fix loop bundle (8 plans) + loop state\nf78cf7b wiki: scope test script to tests/ so bun run test skips bundled qmd/ (item 8)\n---\n{\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0071: required summary field on all 5 template schemas, rendered atop the body, exposed as the --summary create flag\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Add `summary: { type: string, required: true, min: 10, max: 200 }` to the schema block of all five templates/*.md (prd, slice, decision, doc, handoff)\",\n        \"Render a summary line at the top of each template body (under the id/title line)\",\n        \"Confirm createGeneric auto-derives the --summary flag and validation enforces min/max; omitting --summary fails with a missing-required-field error\",\n        \"Update existing test fixtures / create calls that now miss the required summary so the suite stays green\",\n        \"Add a test: create with --summary succeeds and renders the line; create without --summary fails; an existing artifact lacking summary still validates on read (grandfathered)\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0072: generate a static per-project index.md at wiki sync (id, title, summary, status from frontmatter)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"In src/cli/verbs/sync.ts, after the qmd embed loop, scan every artifact under projects/<project>/, read frontmatter (id, title, summary, status, group)\",\n        \"Write projects/<project>/index.md as plain markdown (table or list), sorted by kind then id, linked ids, no prose duplication, NO Dataview/Bases\",\n        \"Idempotent overwrite each sync; create must never write index.md\",\n        \"Add a test against a TEMP vault fixture (follow existing tests/ patterns): sync writes index.md listing the artifacts; re-running yields identical bytes\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0073: group: frontmatter sections the generated index.md (no folders)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Add optional `group: { type: string }` to the kind schemas\",\n        \"In the index.md generator, section artifacts under ## <group> headings; ungrouped fall under ## General\",\n        \"No physical folder nesting; path-containment guard unchanged\",\n        \"Add a test (temp vault): grouped artifacts appear under their group heading, ungrouped under General\",\n        \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n      ],\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"category\": \"chore\",\n      \"description\": \"SLICE-0074: strip template-bleed from all 5 templates (source fix only)\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        \"Read SLICE-0058 first to avoid duplicating the renderer work it already did on existing files\",\n        \"Edit all five templates/*.md: remove the Templater <%* ... %> comment block, the INPUT[select(...)] status widget, and the instructional > blockquotes under each section\",\n        \"Keep clean fixed section headings the author fills, and the summary line added in item 1\",\n---TEMPLATES---\ndecision.md  2.2K\ndoc.md  1.6K\nhandoff.md  1.8K\nprd.md  3.3K\nslice.md  3.6K","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
