{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RPAmBjsd9YkLGaPdN7gt9Q","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttemplate: slice\n3\tversion: 1\n4\tschema:\n5\t  id:              { type: string,    required: true,  pattern: \"SLICE-\\\\d{3,}\" }\n6\t  aliases:         { type: list,      default: [] }\n7\t  title:           { type: string,    required: true,  min: 5, max: 80 }\n8\t  summary:         { type: string,    required: true,  min: 10, max: 200, description: \"One-line scannable summary, rendered atop the body\" }\n9\t  group:           { type: string,    description: \"Optional section heading for this artifact in the generated index.md\" }\n10\t  project:         { type: string,    required: true }\n11\t  parent_prd:      { type: link,      target: prd }\n12\t  status:          { type: enum,      required: true, values: [planned, red, green, closed, blocked, superseded], default: planned }\n13\t  type:            { type: enum,      required: true, values: [HITL, AFK], default: AFK, description: \"HITL = needs human interaction; AFK = agent-completable\" }\n14\t  blocked_by:      { type: link_list, target: slice, default: [] }\n15\t  user_stories:    { type: list,      default: [], description: \"References to PRD user-story IDs covered by this slice\" }\n16\t  acceptance:      { type: list,      required: true, default: [], description: \"Checkboxes; one per criterion. SLICE-006 state machine enforces non-empty before transitioning out of planned.\" }\n17\t  red_log_ref:     { type: file_ref,  description: \"CLI-state path to captured failing-test output; set by `wiki slice red`\" }\n18\t  green_log_ref:   { type: file_ref,  description: \"CLI-state path to captured passing-test output; set by `wiki slice green`\" }\n19\t  review_verdict:  { type: enum,      values: [pass, pass-with-notes, reject], description: \"Set by `wiki slice close` via review-phase skill\" }\n20\t  tdd_exempt:      { type: boolean,   default: false }\n21\t  tdd_exempt_reason: { type: string,  min: 20, description: \"Required when tdd_exempt=true; explains why this slice ships without new tests\" }\n22\t  supersedes:      { type: link,      target: slice }\n23\t  superseded_by:   { type: link,      target: slice }\n24\t  related:         { type: link_list, target: slice, default: [] }\n25\t  force_new_reason:{ type: string,    min: 30, description: \"Required if dedup gate (ADR-0010) was overridden\" }\n26\t  created:         { type: date,      auto: true }\n27\t  updated:         { type: date,      auto: true }\n28\t---\n29\t<!--\n30\t<%*\n31\t// Only runs when created via Templater in Obsidian\n32\tconst title = await tp.system.prompt(\"Title\");\n33\tconst project = await tp.system.prompt(\"Project name\");\n34\tconst parent_prd = await tp.system.prompt(\"Parent PRD (e.g. PRD-001)\");\n35\tconst type = await tp.system.suggester([\"AFK\", \"HITL\"], [\"AFK\", \"HITL\"]);\n36\t-%>\n37\t-->\n38\t# {{title}}\n39\t\n40\t> {{id}} · {{project}} · `INPUT[select(option(planned), option(red), option(green), option(closed), option(blocked), option(superseded)):status]` · `INPUT[select(option(AFK), option(HITL)):type]`\n41\t\n42\t{{summary}}\n43\t\n44\t## Parent\n45\t\n46\t[[{{parent_prd}}]]\n47\t\n48\t## What to build\n49\t\n50\t{{what_to_build}}\n51\t\n52\t> A concise description of this vertical slice. Describe the end-to-end behavior, not layer-by-layer implementation.\n53\t> No file paths. No code snippets except: a prototype snippet that encodes a decision more precisely than prose can. Trim to the decision-rich parts.\n54\t\n55\t## Acceptance criteria\n56\t\n57\t{{#each acceptance}}- [ ] {{this}}\n58\t{{/each}}\n59\t\n60\t## Todo\n61\t\n62\t- [ ] Write tests\n63\t- [ ] Implement feature\n64\t- [ ] Verify acceptance criteria\n65\t\n66\t> Slice close (`wiki slice close`) is gated on every item above being done.\n67\t\n68\t## Blocked by\n69\t\n70\t{{#each blocked_by}}- [[{{this}}]]\n71\t{{else}}None — can start immediately.\n72\t{{/each}}\n73\t\n74\t## Evidence\n75\t\n76\t- **Red log:** {{red_log_ref}}\n77\t- **Green log:** {{green_log_ref}}\n78\t- **Review verdict:** {{review_verdict}}\n79\t\n80\t> Set automatically by the slice state machine. See ADR-0005.\n81\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a24f960-2834-4b0d-82fe-20b82465aea9","uuid":"9909f15b-f362-45a9-aa98-1ae45853339f","timestamp":"2026-06-23T16:47:33.121Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/tothemoon/Dev/code-forge/wiki/templates/slice.md","content":"---\ntemplate: slice\nversion: 1\nschema:\n  id:              { type: string,    required: true,  pattern: \"SLICE-\\\\d{3,}\" }\n  aliases:         { type: list,      default: [] }\n  title:           { type: string,    required: true,  min: 5, max: 80 }\n  summary:         { type: string,    required: true,  min: 10, max: 200, description: \"One-line scannable summary, rendered atop the body\" }\n  group:           { type: string,    description: \"Optional section heading for this artifact in the generated index.md\" }\n  project:         { type: string,    required: true }\n  parent_prd:      { type: link,      target: prd }\n  status:          { type: enum,      required: true, values: [planned, red, green, closed, blocked, superseded], default: planned }\n  type:            { type: enum,      required: true, values: [HITL, AFK], default: AFK, description: \"HITL = needs human interaction; AFK = agent-completable\" }\n  blocked_by:      { type: link_list, target: slice, default: [] }\n  user_stories:    { type: list,      default: [], description: \"References to PRD user-story IDs covered by this slice\" }\n  acceptance:      { type: list,      required: true, default: [], description: \"Checkboxes; one per criterion. SLICE-006 state machine enforces non-empty before transitioning out of planned.\" }\n  red_log_ref:     { type: file_ref,  description: \"CLI-state path to captured failing-test output; set by `wiki slice red`\" }\n  green_log_ref:   { type: file_ref,  description: \"CLI-state path to captured passing-test output; set by `wiki slice green`\" }\n  review_verdict:  { type: enum,      values: [pass, pass-with-notes, reject], description: \"Set by `wiki slice close` via review-phase skill\" }\n  tdd_exempt:      { type: boolean,   default: false }\n  tdd_exempt_reason: { type: string,  min: 20, description: \"Required when tdd_exempt=true; explains why this slice ships without new tests\" }\n  supersedes:      { type: link,      target: slice }\n  superseded_by:   { type: link,      target: slice }\n  related:         { type: link_list, target: slice, default: [] }\n  force_new_reason:{ type: string,    min: 30, description: \"Required if dedup gate (ADR-0010) was overridden\" }\n  created:         { type: date,      auto: true }\n  updated:         { type: date,      auto: true }\n---\n<!--\n<%*\n// Only runs when created via Templater in Obsidian\nconst title = await tp.system.prompt(\"Title\");\nconst project = await tp.system.prompt(\"Project name\");\nconst parent_prd = await tp.system.prompt(\"Parent PRD (e.g. PRD-001)\");\nconst type = await tp.system.suggester([\"AFK\", \"HITL\"], [\"AFK\", \"HITL\"]);\n-%>\n-->\n# {{title}}\n\n> {{id}} · {{project}} · `INPUT[select(option(planned), option(red), option(green), option(closed), option(blocked), option(superseded)):status]` · `INPUT[select(option(AFK), option(HITL)):type]`\n\n{{summary}}\n\n## Parent\n\n[[{{parent_prd}}]]\n\n## What to build\n\n{{what_to_build}}\n\n> A concise description of this vertical slice. Describe the end-to-end behavior, not layer-by-layer implementation.\n> No file paths. No code snippets except: a prototype snippet that encodes a decision more precisely than prose can. Trim to the decision-rich parts.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n{{#each acceptance}}- [ ] {{this}}\n{{/each}}\n\n## Todo\n\n- [ ] Write tests\n- [ ] Implement feature\n- [ ] Verify acceptance criteria\n\n> Slice close (`wiki slice close`) is gated on every item above being done.\n\n## Blocked by\n\n{{#each blocked_by}}- [[{{this}}]]\n{{else}}None — can start immediately.\n{{/each}}\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Red log:** {{red_log_ref}}\n- **Green log:** {{green_log_ref}}\n- **Review verdict:** {{review_verdict}}\n\n> Set automatically by the slice state machine. See ADR-0005.\n","numLines":81,"startLine":1,"totalLines":81}}}
